                                <h3>Biography</h3>
                                <p>Victoria Tanimowo is the founder of Vickies Foundation. She holds a Bachelor’s degree
                                    in accounting from Ghana Technology University College and a Master’s degree in
                                    Globalisation, Business and Development from University of Sussex, United Kingdom.
                                </p>
                                <br><br>
                                <p>Victoria was involved in various extracurricular activities in Ghana Technology
                                    University College and held positions in the International Students Association and
                                    Student Union. While holding these positions, Victoria organised various
                                    self-development programs, leadership seminars, vocational skills training,
                                    entrepreneurial programs, medical check-up, self-defence program for women, football
                                    competitions for women across Universities and a beauty and intellectual pageant to
                                    crown the 2017/2018 Queen for her University.<br><br> Victoria is someone who
                                    recognises the importance of the role of women in the society and understands the
                                    effort needed to further the education of young girls worldwide and in particular in
                                    Africa. On February 10th, 2017, Victoria observed the U.N. International Day of
                                    Women and Girls in STEM by organising a seminar and workshop in her University to
                                    celebrate high school and University Girls in Ghana who have chosen a career path in
                                    the sciences and technology department.</p>
                                <p>Victoria has also served in various NGOs, some of which she still volunteers with
                                    today. She has volunteered with Idea Africa, Ghana, an NGO that concentrates on
                                    helping children read and provides them with libraries and books. She has and still
                                    volunteers with ProfferAid International Foundation Ghana, an NGO focused on
                                    delivering quality health care to people in the rural parts of Ghana; and Camp
                                    Adventure Africa, Nigeria, an NGO equipping young people in the rural parts of
                                    Nigeria with leadership and entrepreneurial skills, with its central focus on
                                    achieving some of the SDGs. She also volunteered with Holland Road Baptist Church,
                                    United Kingdom to provide food and shelter for the homeless.</p>
                                <br><br>
                                <p>She is also the co-founder of Le-Vic Foundation, an NGO she started with her friend
                                    Leticia Sateklah in Ghana which has been reaching out to the homeless, orphanages
                                    and students since October 2017.</p>

