                                    <h5>Reason for the establishment of Vickies Foundation</h5>
                                    <p>“When I applied for my master’s degree, I chose an entirely different course from
                                        what I had wanted to do as a child and what I studied in my bachelor’s degree. I
                                        chose the course because it had the potential of helping me achieve some of my
                                        future goals. Only a week into the course, I was introduced to so many things I
                                        didn’t know were happening all over the world. I have always wanted to help my
                                        country, but I knew very little about the foreign aid policies and structural
                                        adjustment programs of the IMF. This curiosity led me to read more. I discovered
                                        so many things including China’s green revolution program which contributed to
                                        the poverty reduction of the country and then I realised the power and knowledge
                                        that comes with reading and reading the right books!
                                        <br><br>
                                        In Nigeria, we don’t have access to this pool of resources. I therefore thought
                                        of bringing this knowledge to the people, so I decided to create a development
                                        library hub. A few weeks into conceiving the idea, I decided to expand it. I
                                        wanted to start an NGO centred on educating students from disadvantaged schools
                                        during my NYSC (a compulsory scheme for graduates to serve the country before
                                        starting work) but I got my Master’s Degree admission in between and so decided
                                        to halt it. Hence, when the development studies library idea came to mind, I
                                        thought of using the opportunity of starting the NGO at once.”
                                    </p>
                                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                    <h5>About our logo and emblem</h5>
                                    <p>“I sat down and thought to myself, I cannot wait until I achieve all my goals
                                        before I start giving back. I have been very fortunate in the opportunities I
                                        have enjoyed. I therefore want to help others in overcoming the barriers to them
                                        achieving their goals. This stage in life is often difficult to achieve outside
                                        of an enabling environment and so I feel moved to assist others in attaining not
                                        only this level but giving them the opportunity to excel further. So, while I
                                        continue my own journey to the next destination, others will be enabled to
                                        follow and perhaps make a difference in areas I had not even considered.
                                        <br><br>
                                        I now have the experience of completing my master’s degree and am moving to
                                        employment, yet someone else is looking for an opportunity and guidance to do
                                        their master’s degree abroad. I believe my human responsibility is to help that
                                        person achieve that next stage in their dream. I also have a friend who is into
                                        bead making, yet someone lacks the vocational skills to fend for themselves, why
                                        not organise a training workshop and let my friend train people in beads so that
                                        they can also start earning some income? So at every stage of development,
                                        someone else aspires to be there, therefore, it is our collective responsibility
                                        to help lift them a little higher because we are also looking forward to someone
                                        who would take that chance and lift us as we strive to achieve more.<br><br>
                                        This is a new journey for me in Nigeria and I’m willing to contribute my time
                                        and effort to help the children, students and youth realise their dreams.
                                        We hope and pray that what we do will make a positive difference to many and we
                                        pray for God’s blessing on our endeavours.</p>

